For UI/UX work, read `@DESIGN_LANGUAGE.md` and follow the `smart-learnly-ui-ux` skill when available.

Preserve the project’s purple/ink/off-white visual language, selective tactile border/shadow treatment, practical learning-oriented content, accessible interactions, and responsive behaviour. Do not introduce generic AI art, glossy SaaS gradients, a new blue primary, or decorative UI that does not support the task.

